sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller<br/>opendatahub namespace
    participant DNS as Kubernetes DNS<br/>53/UDP
    participant Master as Master/Launcher Pod
    participant Workers as Worker Pods
    participant Volcano as Volcano (optional)<br/>PodGroup CRD

    Note over User,Workers: Flow 1: Distributed PyTorch Training Job Lifecycle

    User->>K8sAPI: 1. kubectl create PyTorchJob<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: 2. Validate PyTorchJob<br/>HTTPS/9443, TLS (self-signed)<br/>API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission response (allow/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: PyTorchJob created

    Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Controller reconciliation loop

    Controller->>K8sAPI: 3. Watch PyTorchJob CR<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: PyTorchJob event

    opt Gang Scheduling Enabled
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create PodGroup CR<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
        K8sAPI->>Volcano: PodGroup scheduling
        Volcano-->>K8sAPI: PodGroup scheduled
    end

    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4a. Create headless Service<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4b. Create Master Pod<br/>(MASTER_ADDR, WORLD_SIZE env vars)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: 4c. Create Worker Pods<br/>(MASTER_ADDR, RANK, WORLD_SIZE env vars)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token

    Workers->>DNS: 5. Resolve master pod DNS<br/>via headless service<br/>UDP/53
    DNS-->>Workers: Master pod IP

    Workers->>Master: 6. Distributed training communication<br/>TCP (per job config)<br/>No encryption (cluster-internal)
    Master-->>Workers: Gradient synchronization

    Note over User,Workers: Flow 2: MPI Job Communication Pattern

    Controller->>K8sAPI: 1. Create ConfigMap (hostfile + scripts)<br/>Create ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token

    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Launcher + Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token

    Note over Master: Launcher Pod init container<br/>copies kubectl binary from<br/>kubectl-delivery image

    Master->>K8sAPI: 3. kubectl exec into workers<br/>HTTPS/443, Per-job SA Token<br/>RBAC: pods/exec on specific pod names
    K8sAPI->>Workers: 4. Execute MPI commands<br/>Kubernetes exec (TLS 1.2+)
    Workers-->>K8sAPI: Command output
    K8sAPI-->>Master: Exec result

    Note over Controller: Job completion/failure detection<br/>Status update, cleanup
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update job status<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
